President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate several individuals for key leadership positions in his administration. Edgard D. Kagan is nominated for the position of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Malaysia. Kagan is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for East Asia and Oceania at the National Security Council. He has previously held various positions in U.S. embassies and the State Department, with experience in countries such as India, Malaysia, Australia, and China. Kagan is fluent in French, Mandarin Chinese, Hungarian, and Spanish.

Nathalie Rayes is nominated for the position of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Croatia. Rayes has had a distinguished career in public service, serving in leadership roles and advocating for various causes. She is currently the President and CEO of Latino Victory and has previously held positions in government, including Deputy Chief of Staff for Los Angeles Mayor James K. Hahn. Rayes has also served on the boards of several organizations and has been recognized for her work. She holds a B.A. in Sociology and an M.P.P. with concentrations in International Relations and Education.

Steven L. Swig is nominated for the position of Member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Swig is a co-founder of Freedom to Prosper, an organization focused on canceling student debt. He has experience in law, specializing in complex antitrust litigation and real estate transactions. Swig has also been involved in various organizations and currently serves on the boards of Solar Electric Light Fund and Americans For Cures, among others.

These nominations reflect President Biden's choices for key leadership positions in his administration, covering areas such as diplomacy, international relations, and economic policy.